The paper deals with image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Support Vector Machines (SVMs), which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained CNNs, which falls under the category of transfer learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of SVMs for classification also falls under the category of supervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with classification and feature extraction, which falls under the category of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category.
